value.0: This elegantly carved chair is both functional and beautiful to look at.
The books lay piled atop each other with little in the way of rhyme or reason, as if someone was interrupted while in the process of returning them to their place.
A pile of books, carelessly discarded.

The following is an excerpt taken from the most recently inscribed page of the book:

"These ancient ruins of Glorag Mur shall do nicely for my exile.  The fool dwarves who used to inhabit this cold cavernous cave complex have left me with the perfect forge below to manufacture my monstrous metallurgical misfits!!  If the Academy were to be so foolish as to persue me...then let them!!  They shall find their downfall here!"

Following the entry are various drawings of academics impaled on mechanized instruments of torture...
This elegantly carved chair is both functional and beautiful to look at.
A pile of books, carelessly discarded.
A pile of books, carelessly discarded.

The following is an excerpt taken from the most recently inscribed page of the book:

"I should no longer fear for them coming for me anymore it seems.  Guarding this level seems a waste of my time.  Perhaps my mindless misguided mechanized minions can do the job for me.  I think my genius would be best spent in the library below figuring out a way to make myself a more....agreeable companion for these long cold nights.....And they called me a madman at the academy!!  Fools!!  After I build 'her', I shall descend from this morbid mountaintop filled with mechanical mental midgets and show those councilmen at the academy what TRUE genius is!! "

The writing trails off here and is replaced by various crude drawings of a giant mechanical woman in various compromising positions....
